
DESCRIPTION:
============

e2retrieve recognize 3 types of part:
 - regular file
 - block device such as a disk or a partition
 - and logical volume (handled via only LVM 2.0)



COMPILATION:
============

Look at config.h to adjust some parameters, then just type 'make'.



USAGE:
======




LIMITATIONS:
===========
* e2retrieve a été conçu pour fonctionner sur PC x86 et ne marchera surement
  pas sur des architectures autres que 32bits et little endian.

* Les structures tronquées ne sont pas analysées finement, donc la demande d'une info
  dans cette structure se soldera par un échec.
  Typiquement superblock et group desc.



HISTORY
=======
Tested on LVM (non-stripped) with 3 disks (13Go, 40GO, 80Go), where the first disk (disk
containing the beginning of the filesystem) crashed (10Go over 130Go). There were possibly
around 40Go data remaining. Most of the files weren't very important : mainly sound and
video files :)
After shortly analysed the ext2 filesystem, the theory seems to say some data recovery
should possible.  and the challenge 



